title: Heart of the Golden West (1942 western) Roy Rogers Writes the Law with Flaming Bullets

sources.title: Heart of the Golden West (1942 western) Roy Rogers Writes the Law with Flaming Bullets
sources.description:
When cattle rustler Ross Lambert (Edmund MacDonald) doubles shipping rates, Roy Rogers (Roy Rogers) gallops into action, recruiting riverboat owner Colonel Popen (Walter Catlett) while dodging bullets and battling bandits beneath a thundering waterfall. Mary Lou (Ruth Terry) finds herself lassoed into danger when Lambert's henchmen snatch her away, but our singing cowboy hero swoops in for a daring rescue that sends the villains sailing straight to the jailhouse!

Original title: Heart of the Golden West (1942)

Colorized version https://youtu.be/d3Cs9pWCruY


Director: Joseph Kane
Writer: Earl Felton
Stars: Roy Rogers, Smiley Burnette, George 'Gabby' Hayes
Genres: Drama, Music, Western
Release date: November 16, 1942
Filming location: Republic Pictures California ranches
